DUAL LICENSING
--------------

The Software is available under a dual-licensing model:

  1. COMMUNITY LICENSE (Open Core)
     The open-source components of this Software are available under the
     GNU Affero General Public License v3 (AGPLv3) for up to nine (9)
     nodes, free of charge, for non-commercial, community, home lab,
     and educational use. See the LICENSE-AGPL file or
     https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html.

  2. COMMERCIAL LICENSE
     Home Lab enthusiasts are encouraged to grow their deployments.
     Once you reach ten (10) or more nodes, you become eligible to
     apply for integration into the QFDM Backend Infrastructure as a
     compensated provider, earning real money for your room, energy,
     and maintenance contributions — subject to meeting basic
     requirements such as proof of electricity bill origin, physical
     safety compliance, and secured hardware access.

    A separate commercial license is required for:
       - Deployments of ten (10) or more nodes
       - Manufacturing, distributing, or renting Codec Terminals
       - Hosting the service as a third-party provider
       - Embedding the Software in proprietary products
       - Any use that directly or indirectly generates revenue
     Commercial licenses may include patent grants, warranties, support,
     and indemnification.

